KCC to Halt South Korean Polysilicon Plant for Maintenance, ICIS Reports

-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e
-- 
2011-04-05T08:06:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/kcc-to-halt-south-korean-polysilicon-plant-for-maintenance-icis-reports.html
KCC Corp. (002380)  plans to shut its joint-
venture polysilicon factory beginning next week for maintenance
that would be completed by late April, the chemical news service
ICIS reported today, citing an unidentified person close to the
company. The plant in  South Korea , which can produce 3,000 tons
a year of the material used in solar panels, is 51 percent owned
by KCC with the remainder held by Hyundai Heavy Industries, the
report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Todd White at 
 twhite2@bloomberg.net  